Hey developers - 3rd person should be an option, not a requirement.  Stupid toons can't navigate their way around trees without about 400 clicks to step around every one inch root sticking up out of the ground, and gods forbid you run into a forest.  Combat is basically click monster, click spell, monster dead or needs half a melee swipe to finish.  Not enough coinage per kill as compared to experience, so you way outlevel your ability to buy skills for many levels.  For the first bunch of levels - there are no aggressive or social mobs, so it's pick mob from a pack of clones, kill mob, rinse, repeat, sit and med, yawn.  Graphics are on par with Diablo 1.  In other words - the engine is already old and any game coming out that didn't slip the release date by 2 years will look like a Formula 1 compared to this Yugo.<br>
<br>
Ah well - half a dozen other games to try soon <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=luxum>Luxum</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Arcanist<BR>Pics plz thx :(</span><br>  Posts: 2124<br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/17/03 8:10:47 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=25555.topic&index=46>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: shadowbane - keeper</span><hr size=1> Quoting myself from the thread in OT:<br>
<br>
I was playing SB for the last week or so, but as a healer (priest) not a wizard type. I like the character system, and even the PvP is suprisingly not as evil as i thought it would be. My biggest gripe is the interface. Oh, so painful. You CAN NOT move with the keyboard. Period. You MUST move with the mouse. This hurts my fingers/wrist/elbow in a very short time, and i have an ergonomic mouse. (In contrast, i can play EQ all day with no discomfort.) You can map certain other functions to the keyboard, but all in all it is very mouse oriented, with a lot of dialog boxes for everything and very few functioning command line text commands. And this kills it for me, as i can't stand to play it for very long before it hurts too much to continue.<br>
<br>
I am just not that into PvP although i could probably grow to enjoy it.  I feel constantly paranoid, but because money is so easy to come by, if you bank regularly, loosing the spare change on your corpse will be no big deal.  It is very satisfying to be able to kill someone when they are being annoying.  If they could fix the ui i might consider this game to be a viable option for me long term... then again i might get bored with nothing to do in the high end except beat up on other people's cities.  Didn't DAoC have a problem with that such that added ome high level PvE content?  Don't kid yourself, SB has some real potential and is very fun to play, especially for people who don't want to spend 3 years getting a character to the max level.  You can feel like you accomplished something in just an hour or so, and if you join an existing group, chances are after level 25 that there is someone in the group who can summon you to them, like CoH except it seems to work worldwide.  If you level really fast, you can level more characters to play around with different classes and have characters to switch to depending on the needs of your guild or group.<br>
<br>
All in all however, i am not subscribing past the first month.  There are too many new MMORPGs coming out, and i am too far along in EQ, to move to a new game that only partially suits me. <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.sillyjanine.com/mybases.html"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.cestusdei.org/uploads/images/luxysig.gif" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=mortainthundercast>Mortain Thundercast</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Visitor</span><br>  Posts: 7<br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/17/03 8:33:49 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=25555.topic&index=47>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.lightofpovar.net/images/wiz1.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: shadowbane - keeper</span><hr size=1> its Ultima Online with a true 3D client, only worse<br>
